msgid "Te suṇanti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.3"
msgid "‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osarissatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.4"
msgid "Te pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharonti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.5"
msgid "‘imaṃ mayaṃ pañhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchissāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.6"
msgid "Evañce no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evamassa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāma; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.7"
msgid "evañcepi no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evampissa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāmā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.8"
msgid "Te suṇanti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.9"
msgid "‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osaṭo’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.10"
msgid "Te yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.11"
msgid "Te bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn89:17.12"
msgid "Te bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā na ceva bhagavantaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, kuto vādaṃ āropessanti? "
msgstr "They don’t even get around to asking their question to the Buddha, so how could they refute his answer? "

msgctxt "mn89:17.13"
msgid "Aññadatthu bhagavantaṃyeva okāsaṃ yācanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya. "
msgstr "Invariably, they ask the ascetic Gotama for the chance to go forth. "

msgctxt "mn89:17.14"
msgid "Te bhagavā pabbājeti. "
msgstr "And he gives them the going-forth. "

msgctxt "mn89:17.15"
msgid "Te tathāpabbajitā samānā ekā vūpakaṭṭhā appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharantā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti. "
msgstr "Soon after going forth, living withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, they realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "mn89:17.16"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "They say: "

msgctxt "mn89:17.17"
msgid "‘manaṃ vata, bho, anassāma; manaṃ vata, bho, panassāma’. "
msgstr "‘We were almost lost! We almost perished! "

msgctxt "mn89:17.18"
msgid "Mayañhi pubbe assamaṇāva samānā samaṇāmhāti paṭijānimhā, abrāhmaṇāva samānā brāhmaṇāmhāti paṭijānimhā, anarahantova samānā arahantāmhāti paṭijānimhā. "
msgstr "For we used to claim that we were ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones, but we were none of these things. "

msgctxt "mn89:17.19"
msgid "‘Idāni khomha samaṇā, idāni khomha brāhmaṇā, idāni khomha arahanto’ti. "
msgstr "But now we really are ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones!’ "

msgctxt "mn89:17.20"
msgid "Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti: "
msgstr "So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching: "

msgctxt "mn89:17.21"
msgid "‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, pts-vp-pli2.124, sc10
#. VAR: jīvikāya → jīvitassa (bj) | jīvikaṃ (bj-a) | jīvitaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn89:18.1"
msgid "Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo mamabhattā mamayānā, ahaṃ nesaṃ jīvikāya dātā, yasassa āhattā; "
msgstr "Furthermore, these chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa share my meals and my carriages. I give them a livelihood and bring them renown. "

msgctxt "mn89:18.2"
msgid "atha ca pana no tathā mayi nipaccakāraṃ karonti yathā bhagavati. "
msgstr "And yet they don’t show me the same level of devotion that they show to the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn89:18.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, bhante, senaṃ abbhuyyāto samāno ime ca isidattapurāṇā thapatayo vīmaṃsamāno aññatarasmiṃ sambādhe āvasathe vāsaṃ upagacchiṃ. "
msgstr "Once it so happened that while I was leading a military campaign and testing Isidatta and Purāṇa I took up residence in a cramped house. "

#. VAR: kathāya vītināmetvā, yato ahosi bhagavā → assosuṃ kho bhagavantaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn89:18.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya vītināmetvā, yato ahosi bhagavā tato sīsaṃ katvā maṃ pādato karitvā nipajjiṃsu. "
msgstr "They spent most of the night discussing the teaching, then they lay down with their heads towards where the Buddha was and their feet towards me. "

msgctxt "mn89:18.5"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to me: "

msgctxt "mn89:18.6"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho. "
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn89:18.7"
msgid "Ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo mamabhattā mamayānā, ahaṃ nesaṃ jīvikāya dātā, yasassa āhattā; "
msgstr "These chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa share my meals and my carriages. I give them a livelihood and bring them renown. "

msgctxt "mn89:18.8"
msgid "atha ca pana no tathā mayi nipaccakāraṃ karonti yathā bhagavati. "
msgstr "And yet they don’t show me the same level of devotion that they show to the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn89:18.9"
msgid "Addhā ime āyasmanto tassa bhagavato sāsane uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ jānantī’ti. "
msgstr "Clearly these venerables have realized a higher distinction in the Buddha’s instructions than they had before.’ "

msgctxt "mn89:18.10"
msgid "Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti: "
msgstr "So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching: "

msgctxt "mn89:18.11"
msgid "‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc11
msgctxt "mn89:19.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavāpi khattiyo, ahampi khattiyo; "
msgstr "Furthermore, the Buddha is an aristocrat, and so am I. "

msgctxt "mn89:19.2"
msgid "bhagavāpi kosalo, ahampi kosalo; "
msgstr "The Buddha is Kosalan, and so am I. "

msgctxt "mn89:19.3"
msgid "bhagavāpi āsītiko, ahampi āsītiko. "
msgstr "The Buddha is eighty years old, and so am I. "

msgctxt "mn89:19.4"
msgid "Yampi, bhante, bhagavāpi khattiyo ahampi khattiyo, bhagavāpi kosalo ahampi kosalo, bhagavāpi āsītiko ahampi āsītiko; "
msgstr "Since this is so, "

msgctxt "mn89:19.5"
msgid "imināvārahāmevāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavati paramanipaccakāraṃ kātuṃ, mittūpahāraṃ upadaṃsetuṃ. "
msgstr "it’s proper for me to show the Buddha such utmost devotion and demonstrate such friendship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20
msgctxt "mn89:20.1"
msgid "Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma; "
msgstr "Well, now, sir, I must go. "

msgctxt "mn89:20.2"
msgid "bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti. "
msgstr "I have many duties, and much to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn89:20.3"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, great king, go at your convenience.” "

msgctxt "mn89:20.4"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, pts-vp-pli2.125, sc12
msgctxt "mn89:21.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantassa rañño pasenadissa kosalassa bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Soon after the king had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "mn89:21.2"
msgid "“eso, bhikkhave, rājā pasenadi kosalo dhammacetiyāni bhāsitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before he got up and left, King Pasenadi spoke shrines to the teaching. "

msgctxt "mn89:21.3"
msgid "Uggaṇhatha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni; "
msgstr "Learn these shrines to the teaching! "

msgctxt "mn89:21.4"
msgid "pariyāpuṇātha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni; "
msgstr "Memorize these shrines to the teaching! "

msgctxt "mn89:21.5"
msgid "dhāretha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni. "
msgstr "Remember these shrines to the teaching! "

msgctxt "mn89:21.6"
msgid "Atthasaṃhitāni, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni ādibrahmacariyakānī”ti. "
msgstr "These shrines to the teaching are beneficial and relate to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn89:21.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn89:21.8"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn89:21.9"
msgid "Dhammacetiyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

